Feature: the canonical lead CLAUDE.md primer directs the router to open the product-discovery conversation as a general brainstorming conversation first, then branch into a router-selected structured discovery skill

  lead-vglj (P2) — product authority 2026-06-29: "for the lead to detect when the
  repo is effectively empty and start a product discovery conversation with the
  user to start determining the shape of the new system."

  This scenario pins the OPENER SHAPE. SCOPE PINNED 2026-06-30 (product authority,
  David): the opener is a GENERAL BRAINSTORMING conversation FIRST, then BRANCHES
  into ONE structured discovery skill — selected from jobs-to-be-done,
  problem-framing-canvas, opportunity-solution-tree, or customer-journey-map —
  based on what surfaces in the brainstorming conversation. It is NOT a fixed
  single skill chosen up front. The router performs the skill SELECTION itself, at
  the router / main-agent level, as the triage step that follows the brainstorming
  opener, then dispatches the selected discovery skill.

  Split out of the proactive-initiation trigger scenario to keep one behavior per
  scenario.

  CORPUS GAP (follow-up for lead-22x1): there is no dedicated "brainstorming" /
  divergence-opener skill in the skills corpus today, so the opener is encoded as
  router-level behavior with skill-selection as the triage step. A named
  brainstorming/divergence opener skill is a candidate skills-corpus follow-up.

  AUTHORING ONLY — no BC dispatch. @bc tag is the Architect's to apply at
  assignment time; @lead_integration:templates below is provisional placement
  matching sibling primer-furniture scenarios.

